result.name: JoonGo House Korean Restaurant

reviews.text: Fantastic little Korean restaurant with amazing fresh food, good service, kind staff and good prices! I love this place! Worth the time to find!
Good for lunch with friends. Eat and talk, no time limit as in most locals.

A small cosy Koeean restaurant that serves authentic Korean side dish when you place order from the main menu. Side dish includes a selection of kimchi, toufu, bean sprout, tiny fired fish, seasoned potato and etc. From the main menu, there are vegetable wraps to go wirh pan fried meat, ginseng soup, bibimbab just to name a few.

My favorite go to place for homemade style Korean food! With an affordable price, you can get a really good deal here especially if u order one that comes with banchan! You'll be surprised cause some items comes with up to 6 different side dishes excluding the ‘main dish’ you ordered! All in all definitely a must try and if you need convincing, you'll see some Korean middle aged men eating here for dinner! That proofs the authenticity!

Have to say I’ll be extra careful about high google reviews next time. It’s basically bare minimum and not worth the price.
1) Came all the way here for cold noodles after reading those generous reviews. The dishes are quite overpriced; for $90 HKD I kinda had high expectations on their cold noodles because in HK you usually pay for $50 and lower for real good noodles. However, after trying the side dishes (kimchi, bean sprout, potatoes), I already knew the food won’t be as authentic/good. Even my mom can make better kimchi. When the cold noodles came, I was surprised to see how plain it was. Literally just cold noodles and chunks of ice cubes. The taste? Can’t be more tasteless and I ended up pouring in the kimchi side dish to get some flavours. 
2) Service was not worth the 10% tips. U don’t feel welcomed and when I asked about the dishes the waiter said he didn’t know what the dish is like (like really?) No water refill either. The female owner does look nice tho.
3) The only positive experience is that the l environment is pretty neat and cozy

result.name: Joon Go House Korean Restaurant

reviews.text: Not bad at all. Spicy cold noodle (actually not cold but just room temperature) was very chewy. Rice bowl was colorful and abundance.
So so food, small portion for the price (dinner set), questionable hygiene (found an eyelash on the side dish, gave it back, and the same dish came back minus the lash)
Clean nice food. Very good :)

The environment is great, look like and with nice style.
However, the staff (owner?) who help on order is not nice, but other staffs are friendly.  And their food just average, although outside always queue for tables, but not as good as expected.
And the kimchi is extremely salty, not sure it is in traditional style or over seasoned
Love the food here

result.name: 純子餐廳

reviews.text: Fantastic little Korean restaurant with amazing fresh food, good service, kind staff and good prices! I love this place! Worth the time to find!
Good for lunch with friends. Eat and talk, no time limit as in most locals.

原來店子成立於1984年，我這才第一次光顧。好吃！由前菜已經是好好吃，真的是每款也有自己的味道。做的是傳統韓國料理，不設燒烤，正合我意。試過了人蔘雞湯，如果是一般的貨式，基本上都用現成的，未入口都已經溶晒，但這間不會，有咬口的，應該是老闆自制的，湯不需再加鹽，有鮮味。牛筋骨煲落了很多香料，四大塊牛肋骨，好Juicy，辣的，少見。地點是辟靜了一點，但這樣才不至於捱貴租，好店子，一定再來支持。到時再作補充。

食物很有傳統韓國家庭的感覺，但價錢偏貴 ! 
VERY GOOD KOREAN STYLE FOOD AND HOME FEEL , BUT ARE BIT EXPENSTIVE !
